Detailed Description

Contain all the data about an item on the map.

An item is e.g. a piece of an street (like street_rec in MapCentral), a forest, a lake.

void Item::setGfxData (  GfxData *  gfx,
bool  deleteOld = false
) 
 

Set the geographical representation to a new value.

NB! The given gfxData is not copied, and must therefore not be deleted by the caller.

Warning:
The old GfxData will not be deleted since it might be allocated by an allocator in the map. Sa if the old GfxData is allocated elsewhere this might introduce a memory leak.
Parameters:
gfx The new gfxData that have the georaphical information about this item.

uint32 Item::m_localID [protected]
 

The local id of this item.

The first bit (bit 0) is used for identify node0 or node1 (this means that the first bit is unused for every item except for the subclass "StreetSegmentItem"). Bit 1 to 4 shows on what zoomlevel this item is significant.
